John Charles Makurdi Two people are feared dead in a renewed clash between residents of Oju and Konshisha local government areas of Benue State. Sources said that a farmer from Konshisha LGA had last week strayed into the farm of  another farmer at Okpute LGA which led  to a fight. A source said, “But the incident of Tuesday was unprovoked, the Tiv people invaded Igede community and burnt down our houses. Two people were killed. The Ter Ikyor in Konshisha LGA, Chief Thomas Gbinde, confirmed the attack. But the state police command spokesperson, DSP, Catherine Anene said, “There was no crisis; there was only threat but police came to have a dialogue with them. Nobody died.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 